<item>
            <title>[OAK-2010] BlobGcMaxAgeInSecs is set to high for MongoBlobStore</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-2010</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Whilst working with MongoMk had problems with BlobGarbageCollector, it didn&apos;t remove redundant blobs at all.&lt;br/&gt;
When enabled debug logging I found the following entry in log files:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;30.07.2014 19:23:32.922 *DEBUG* [pool-5-thread-2] org.apache.jackrabbit.oak.plugins.blob.MarkSweepGarbageCollector &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt; of blobs present in BlobStore : [0] which have been last modified before [2011-11-03 18:23:32.922]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looks that GC is considering only 3 years old blobs by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
